  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(48) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Their brethren also the Levites.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—That is, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Levites who were not musicians",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the remaining Levites.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Appointed.—Literally, given—that is, to Aaron and his sons as their assistants; Numbers 3:9 (Heb.), “And thou shalt give the Levites to Aaron and to his sons, given are they to him from amongst the sons of Israel.” The word is nethûnîm. (Comp. nethînim, an identical form, as the name of a well-known class of Temple-servants.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Appointed.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Literally, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "given—",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "that is, to Aaron and his sons as their assistants; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 3:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (Heb.), “And thou shalt give the Levites to Aaron and to his sons, given are they to him from amongst the sons of Israel.” The word is ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "nethûnîm.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "nethînim,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " an identical form, as the name of a well-known class of Temple-servants.)",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Tabernacle.—Rather, dwelling-place (mishkan).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Tabernacle.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Rather, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "dwelling-place ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "mishkan",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ")",
            "children": []
